headlines.description: — Pascal Siakam scored 22 points, Tyrese Haliburton had 21 points and nine assists, and the Indiana Pacers snapped a three-game losing streak with a 115-103 victory over the Washington Wizards on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Pacers end 3-game skid, extend Wizards losing streak to 11 with 115-103 victory

headlines.description: — Jimmy Butler scored a season-high 33 points, leading the Miami Heat past the Dallas Mavericks 123-118 in overtime on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Butler scores season-high 33, Heat hold off Mavericks 123-118 in OT

headlines.description: — James Harden had 23 points and eight assists, Ivica Zubac had 16 points and 12 rebounds and the Los Angeles Clippers coasted to a 125-99 win over the Philadelphia 76ers on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: James Harden scores 23 points to lead Clippers to rout over his old 76ers team, 125-99

headlines.description: — Cam Thomas scored 34 points and the Brooklyn Nets beat the Kings 108-103 on Sunday night in Nets coach Jordi Fernandez's return to Sacramento.
headlines.shortLinkText: Cam Thomas scores 34 points and Nets beat Kings 108-103
